main event: A distant object appeared as a point of bright light, blinking at irregular intervals, moving at a rapid speed before disappearing.
interesting points: The object's high speed, blinking, and eventual disappearance are consistent with a meteorological phenomenon, such as a meteor or comet.
This was the only report received of an object seen in this area.
The location of the sighting was in the Pacific Ocean at coordinates 35.50N 152.50W.
The object was concluded to be 'UNKNOWN' by the source.
No photographs were provided with the report.
